  "assay": "10x Chromium Single Cell 3' Gene Expression",
  "title": "10x 3' scRNA-seq (v3)",
  "description": "Droplet-based single-cell 3' gene-expression profiling on Illumina. Cells are partitioned into gel-bead emulsions (GEMs); mRNA is barcoded during reverse transcription with a per-cell 16 nt barcode + 12 nt UMI, and the amplified cDNA is fragmented and built into a P5/P7-indexed short-read library. Profiles the transcriptomes of thousands of single cells per run.",
